{"key":"post-13238266","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13238266</id>\n<content>1:10 is perfect with properly pasteurized chopped or shredded straw.&amp;nbsp; Just eyeball it or figure roughly ten handfuls of straw per handful of crumbled up cake.&amp;nbsp; It also helps to put a weight on top of the tray after spawning to hold the straw compressed during colonization.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Be careful with straw in a kitty litter tray.&amp;nbsp; It will continue to drain water after pasteurization for a few days.&amp;nbsp; You'll want holes in the tray to let this water drain or you're going to have problems with the bottom not colonizing properly.&amp;nbsp; If you do it this way, I'd dump the straw block out of the tray a week or so after full colonization and fruit it like a giant cake without the tray.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13238405</next>\n<prev>13237491</prev>\n<first>13236152</first>\n<last>13241248</last>\n<when>1285297012</when>\n<utime>09/24/10 05:56 AM</utime>\n</post>"}